claims:
Claims 1. A method of delivering energy to an ultrasonic device, the ultrasonic device comprising an electromechanical ultrasonic system defined by a predetermined resonant frequency, the electromechanical ultrasonic system further comprising an ultrasonic transducer coupled to an ultrasonic blade, the method comprising: applying, by a processor or control circuit, energy to the ultrasonic blade at a first power level P1 via the ultrasonic transducer coupled to the ultrasonic blade; measuring, by the processor or control circuit, a complex impedance of the ultrasonic transducer; receiving, by the processor or control circuit a complex impedance feedback data point; comparing, by the processor or control circuit, the complex impedance feedback data point to a reference complex impedance characteristic pattern; and determining, by the processor or control circuit, that the ultrasonic blade is contacting a vessel based on the results of the comparison. 2. The method of claim 1 , further comprising: disabling, by the processor or control circuit, power applied to the ultrasonic transducer; and switching, by the processor or control circuit, to a second power level P2 that is lower than the first power level P1. 3. The method of claim 2, further comprising generating, by the processor or control circuit, a warning that the ultrasonic blade is contacting a vessel. 4. The method of claim 3, wherein generating, by the processor or control circuit, a warning that the ultrasonic blade is contacting a vessel comprises emitting, by the processor or control circuit, a warning light. 5. The method of claim 3, wherein generating, by the processor or control circuit, a warning that the ultrasonic blade is contacting a vessel comprises emitting, by the processor or control circuit, a warning sound. 6. The method of claim 1 , wherein determining, by the processor or control circuit, that the ultrasonic blade is contacting a vessel comprises: 

